(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on explaining how a useful trait becomes common.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in adaptation, variation, and natural selection that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Evolution step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on adaptation and selection reasoning.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid thinking individuals evolve during their lifetime while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Evolution: adaptation, variation, and natural) Tj
T*
(selection.) Tj
T*
(- Thinking individuals evolve during their lifetime.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Evolution without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Evolution in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around adaptation and selection reasoning before trying) Tj
T*
(harder tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as thinking individuals evolve during their lifetime and) Tj
T*
(write the correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Evolution regularly so the method behind adaptation, variation, and natural) Tj
T*
(selection becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Evolution and describe how it fits into Biology.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on explaining how a useful trait becomes common and) Tj
T*
(explain each step.) Tj
T*
(- Describe why thinking individuals evolve during their lifetime causes errors and how) Tj
T*
(to avoid it.) Tj
T*
(- Answer an exam-style question that focuses on adaptation and selection reasoning.) Tj
T*
